@startuml pipeline

' The pipeline Rehearse and Deploy share, drawn once so neither path diagram
' repeats it. Survey (read-only) requires each Session Clone, walks it for
' its Contribution, and folds them into a validated Manifest: the single
' site a colliding federation is rejected. Build integrates the Manifest and the
' Contributor sources into a self-contained Artifact (collected files plus the
' integrated CLI carried as installable wheels, resolvable against those wheels
' and public PyPI alone). Install places the Artifact at a Destination. The two
' operations differ only in that Destination, so this spine is path-agnostic;
' the Rehearse and Deploy diagrams open from it and show only their own tail.

!include elements.puml

title Ringmaster: shared deploy pipeline (Survey → Build → Install)

left to right direction

rectangle "Survey"    as survey   <<phase>>
rectangle "Manifest"  as manifest <<artifact>>
rectangle "Build"     as build    <<phase>>
rectangle "Install"   as install  <<phase>>

registry --> survey   : ""[repos]""
clone    --> survey   : Contribution

survey   --> manifest : produces
manifest --> build    : drives
build    --> uv       : build carried wheels
build    --> artifact : produces

artifact --> install  : placed by
install  --> uv       : install ""vv""\n(carried wheels + public index)

note right of install : produces a Host or Rehearsal Installation:\nsee the Deploy and Rehearse diagrams

' Drop UL elements declared in elements.puml but not referenced here, so the
' rendered SVG carries no orphan boxes.
remove @unlinked

@enduml
